</span></code></pre></div></div>

<hr />
<h2 id="constructing-user-defined-functions-in-r">Constructing user-defined functions in R</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>To find out about built-in functions use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">help(&lt;function_name&gt;)</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">?&lt;function_name&gt;</code>, or <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">example(&lt;function_name&gt;)</code> command</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Syntax for creating your own function <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;f_name&gt; &lt;- function(&lt;params&gt;){&lt;body&gt;}</code></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<div class="language-R highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">f</span><span class="o">&lt;-</span><span class="k">function</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">){</span><span class="n">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="o">^</span><span class="m">2</span><span class="p">)}</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="m">9</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="m">1</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="m">81</span><span class="w">
</span></code></pre></div></div>

